EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to crimes; revising provisions relating to the crime
of assault; providing a penalty; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law defines the crime of assault as: (1) unlawfully attempting to use
2 physical force against another person; or (2) intentionally placing another person in
3 reasonable apprehension of immediate bodily harm. (NRS 200.471) This bill
4 revises the definition of the crime of assault to clarify that intentionally placing
5 another person in reasonable apprehension of immediate bodily harm includes,
6 without limitation, making a threat of sexual violence against another person.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
